{
  "stem": "1684.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And deportations-- in 1942, after we were married already, on Rosh Hashana.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were married in July 1942, and on Rosh Hashana 1942, there was another deportation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "At that time, my husband already got to be the organizer of a company which was called Madritsch.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I got a job by Madritsch.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We made uniforms and civil clothes by Madritsch.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was out-- they formed the ghetto already-- and it was outside from the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were taken every day from our apartment, which was in the ghetto, to the working place by Madritsch outside the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And now, there was another deportation coming up.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my husband knew-- a friend of his had a company outside from the ghetto in a little-- like a little house, it was, and it had an upstairs like-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] like a little-- the upstairs, what is-- what can it be called?",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was one magazine, like a-- like a-- like a store, and then there was, on top, there was another little thing to sit on.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then there was a basement, which was deep, very deep, only dirt, like.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But we went into this little house-- it was Rosh Hashana-- with one seder.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we took in some water, and we took in some bread, and some sugar-- sugar cubes.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We were-- I don't know how many people, we were a lot of people there, but not as many as the next time we were hiding.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But anyhow, my husband will tell you this story of how it-- how I came out again from there.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Anyhow, we were sitting there.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
